```json
{
  "application": "Snakemake",
  "software": [
    "Singularity",
    "MANTIS",
    "GATK",
    "Snakemake"
  ],
  "resources": [
    "TNRunner dataBundle",
    "Homo_sapiens_assembly38.fasta",
    "Homo_sapiens_assembly38.dict",
    "Homo_sapiens_assembly38.fasta.fai",
    "MSI6.sorted.bed",
    "tumor.bam/tumor.bai/normal.bam/normal.bai",
    "tumor.cram/tumor.crai/normal.cram/normal.crai"
  ],
  "requirements": [
    "slurm",
    "AWS EC2 (optional)",
    "S3 (optional)"
  ],
  "description": "This script is a Snakemake workflow for MSI status calculation using the MANTIS tool. It requires a TNRunner dataBundle, a singularity container, and input bam/bai or cram/crai files. It can be run on a local server or via slurm's sbatch. The script also provides instructions on how to run it on AWS EC2 via the JobRunner."
}
```
